I"ú<h1 id="global-variables">Global variables</h1>

<pre><code class="language-python3">
x = "global"

def foo():
    print("x inside:", x)


foo()
print("x outside:", x)

# Output

x inside: global
x outside: global

</code></pre>

<h1 id="non-local-variables">Non local variables</h1>

<p>The nonlocal keyword is used to work with variables inside nested functions, where the variable should not belong to the inner function.</p>

<p>Use the keyword `nonlocal to declare that the variable is not local.</p>
